@HdkTech¬† The print quality is more on par with that of the X1C.
In terms of mechanicals The CC already comes with hardened steel gears and a hardened nozzle, which I believe on the P1S is just stainless.
Print times on the CC are also a lot faster than that of the P1S and the screen is nicer. The hotter nozzle and bed on the CC should also make it easier to print more demanding materials like PC or glass\carbon filled materials.

